# Root-anchored (leading slash) ON PURPOSE: this ignores a project's private
# working-memory folder if one ever appears at the repo root, but must NOT
# match the plugin's own `plugins/gru953-studio/skills/dev-memory/` skill.
# Without the leading slash, `Dev-Memory/` matched that skill folder
# case-insensitively on macOS (git core.ignorecase=true), so the skill was
# silently never committed — the published plugin shipped with 5 skills, not
# 6, and CI failed on a clean Linux checkout. 2026-07-11 fix.
/Dev-Memory/
node_modules/
.DS_Store
*.log
.env
.env.*
plugins/*.zip
